This paper is primarily focused on network security and cryptography, which suggests that it would likely fall under the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a novel system for identifying key exchange protocols using a multi-resolution approach and generating scalable fingerprints, which could potentially fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper uses experimental evidence to demonstrate the effectiveness of their approach, which could also fall under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
